So what is ArrayRankTwoAux inheriting from?
You want to make sure to inherit from an array auxkernel, as only those have a computeValue that returns an array.
A good example is the FunctionArrayAux, with the computeValue below:
RealEigenVector
FunctionArrayAux::computeValue()
{
  RealEigenVector v(_var.count());
  const Point & p = isNodal() ? *_current_node : _q_point[_qp];
  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _var.count(); ++i)
    v(i) = _funcs[i]->value(_t, p);
  return v;
}

how do you diagnose that the function isnt being updated?
In what object are you using it?
